{{draft}}{{Infobox religious building| religious_affiliation = ]][[Shinto]]| image                 = | map_type              = Japan| coordinates           = | map_size              = | map_alt               = | map_relief            = | map_caption           = | location              = | festival              = | consecration_year     = | type                  = '']][[Gokoku shrine]]''<br />(Formerly '']][[Shokonsha]]'')| leadership            = | website               = | architecture_style    = | founded_by            = | established           = | date_destroyed        = }}{{Interlanguage link|{{PAGENAME}}|simple||ja|松前護國神社}} (松前護國神社) is a ]][[Shinto shrine]] located in ]][[Japan]]. <!-- it is not a Beppyo shrine --> It is a ]][[Gokoku Shrines|Gokoku Shrine]], or a shrine dedicated to war dead.{{Efn|Is this ]][[WP:BLUE]] considering that the shrine is literally named as such?}} Such shrines were made to serve to enshrine the war dead, and they were all considered "branches" of ]][[Yasukuni Shrine]]. They were renamed from ]][[Shōkonsha|Shokonsha]] in 1939.<ref>{{Cite journal |last=TAKAYAMA |first=K. PETER |date=1990 |title=Enshrinement and Persistency of Japanese Religion |url=https://www.jstor.org/stable/23917081 |journal=Journal of Church and State |volume=32 |issue=3 |pages=527–547 |issn=0021-969X}}</ref><!-- derived from content I added to ]][[Gokoku shrines]] from an english source -->Matsumae Gokoku Shrine is a Shinto shrine located in Matsumae, Hokkaido, Japan. Gokoku shrines, originally known as Shokonsha, were established during the Meiji Restoration to honor individuals who died in wars, serving as local branches of the central Yasukuni Shrine in Tokyo. <ref>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gokoku_Shrines?utm_source=chatgpt.com</ref>Situated near Matsumae Castle, the northernmost castle in Japan, Matsumae Gokoku Shrine is part of a historic area that includes other notable sites such as Matsumae Shrine and the Buddhist temple Ryūun-in. <ref>https://mapcarta.com/W647365281?utm_source=chatgpt.com</ref>Visitors to Matsumae Gokoku Shrine can explore the rich history of the region, with the shrine serving as a place of remembrance for those who sacrificed their lives in service to the nation. The surrounding area offers a glimpse into Japan's feudal past, with Matsumae Castle and other cultural landmarks nearby.For those interested in visiting, the shrine is accessible by a short walk from the Matsuki bus stop. The address is 145 Matsushiro, Matsumae-chō, Matsumae-gun, Hokkaido. <ref>https://map.uu-hokkaido.jp/e/matsumae-shrine/?utm_source=chatgpt.com</ref>Please note that information about Matsumae Gokoku Shrine is limited, and visitors are encouraged to explore the site in person to fully appreciate its historical and cultural significance== See Also ==* ]][[Controversies surrounding Yasukuni Shrine]]* ]][[Martyrs' shrines (China)|Martyr's Shrines]]* ]][[:en:Martial temple|Martial temple]] and ]][[:en:Wen Wu temple|Wen Wu temple]]* ]][[National Revolutionary Martyrs' Shrine]]* ]][[Eternal Spring Shrine]]* ]][[:en:Chinese Cultural Renaissance|Chinese Cultural Renaissance]]* ]][[Ancestral shrine]]* ]][[:en:Gallant Garden|Gallant Garden]]* ]][[Gokoku Shrines]]* ]][[:en:Tomb of the Unknown Soldier|Tomb of the Unknown Soldier]]* ]][[:en:Arlington National Cemetery|Arlington National Cemetery]]* ]][[:en:Valhalla|Valhalla]] (home to the souls of fallen warriors in Scandinavian mythology)* ]][[:en:Walhalla (memorial)|Walhalla Shrine]] (a hall of fame in Germany honoring "commendable and honorable Germans")* ]][[Eternal Spring Shrine]]* ]][[The common end of myriad good deeds]]* ]][[:en:Greek hero cult|Greek hero cult]]== Notes =={{Notelist}}== References =={{reflist}}{{Draft categories|]][[Category:Gokoku shrines]]]][[category:unsorted completion categories]]{{Gokoku shrines}}]][[Category:Gokoku shrines]]]][[category:unsorted completion categories]]]][[Category:Unsorted completion categories]]]][[Category:Unsorted completion categories]]]][[Category:bump-01-18]]]][[Category:bump1-19]]]][[Category:refreshing categories imported on 2024-01-19]]]][[Category:bump 1-20]]]][[Category:dd]]]][[Category:Mass editing to refresh the first new Wikipedia redirects]]]][[Category:properly attributed pages]]]][[Category:Matsumae Gokoku Shrine]]]][[Category:properly attributed pages]]]][[en:Matsumae Gokoku Shrine]]<!--this page is not from a simple english wikipedia draft. Categorizing it as such was an error. It is from an archived english wikipedia draft-->]][[ja:松前護國神]]}}{{⚠️🚨COPIED from EverybodyWiki ❗❕⚠️😡😤Please respect Licence CC-BY-SA ❗}}{{Source Wikipedia}}

